data.title: mobb deep Archives
data.text:
For the first time since the death of Albert “Prodigy” Johnson, his Mobb Deep partner, Kejuan “Havoc” Muchita took to the stage to perform some of the duo’s classic songs. Havoc and other stars gathered on stage to honor Prodigy as part of the Newark, New Jersey stop of the Art of Rap Festival tour stop on […]

Of all people, Master P is calling out BET for what he feels was a disingenuine tribute to Prodigy of Mobb Deep.

The passing of Mobb Deep’s Prodigy this week took the Hip-Hop culture by surprise and the outpouring that followed the news has been heartfelt and touching to say the least.

The news that Albert “Prodigy” Johnson of Mobb Deep fame has died is still rippling through social media, with colleagues and fans alike of the crew pouring out their hearts. The Hip-Hop community has taken to Twitter, Instagram, and other outlets to express their grief for the 42-year-old wordsmith, who was battling sickle cell anemia […]

Prodigy, who makes up one-half of the longtime rap duo Mobb Deep, took fans for quite a turn with the release of his 2011 autobiography, My Infamous Life: The Autobiography of Mobb Deep’s Prodigy. Next year, the Hempstead, Long Island native aims to release both a prison-themed cookbook and a follow-up memoir.

**Update** Just like that, Complex has premiered the “Survival Of The Fittest” 2K15 Remix which also appear on a new EP of the same name. 1. Hide Away Produced By Havoc 2. Survival Of The Fittest (ESPN Remix) Produced By Havoc & Additional Keys By Yung Fokus 3. Whats Going On Produced By Havoc 4. […]

Havoc, one-half of the legendary Mobb Deep, crafted a new EP, 13 Reloaded, which releases on November 18. From the project, the veteran MC and producer debuts “What I Rep,” featuring The LOX’s own Sheek Louch.
